    <section class="section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <div class="cards">
        <div class="card">
          <p>
            A full-day pirate-themed loop from Duck down NC-12 to Hatteras, exploring shipwreck lore at the
            <a href="https://graveyardoftheatlantic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Graveyard of the Atlantic Museum</a>,
            visiting the <a href="https://www.nps.gov/caha/planyourvisit/chls.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cape Hatteras Light Station</a>,
            then back north for dinner at the
            <a href="https://jollyrogerobx.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Jolly Roger Restaurant</a>.
          </p>
          <ul class="list">
            <li><strong>Driving (total):</strong> ~4.5‚Äì5.5 hrs depending on traffic/winds (NC-12).</li>
            <li><strong>Theme touches:</strong> shipwreck exhibits, lighthouse grounds, beach lookouts, pirate-y dinner vibe.</li>
            <li><strong>Note:</strong> Lighthouse <em>climb</em> is paused for restoration in 2025; grounds and area are open.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="rule"></div>

